Lovely ambience, but very expensive. The flow of tapas delivery was not fluid and was slow. They accommodated food allergies nicely.  Some dishes, such as the Thai sundried beef , were very good. Others, such as the kohlapuri chicken, were very mediocre. The wine prices were ridiculously high.

Some of the dishes were very good including the Thai beef tapas dish and the panang curry however other items were quite average and the flow of service for a tapas restaurant was snail-paced. The restaurant's ambiance was great with fabulous artwork and a cool vibe, but the food could have been much better for the price.

Some of the Indian-inspired items taste better here than in the Indian restaurants in town. Items I liked: kohlapuri chicken wings, tandoori qail with mint raita, red-snapper and shrimp in kerela curry, lex grandfather chichen curry, dahl.
